org.eclipse.ui

Class MultiPartInitException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.eclipse.core.runtime.CoreException
          • org.eclipse.ui.WorkbenchException
            • org.eclipse.ui.MultiPartInitException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class MultiPartInitException
extends WorkbenchException
    A checked exception indicating one or more workbench parts could not be initialized correctly. The message text provides a further description of the problem.
    Since:
    3.5
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
    Restriction:
    This class is not intended to be subclassed by clients.

        public MultiPartInitException(IWorkbenchPartReference[] references,
                              PartInitException[] exceptions)
        Creates a new exception object. Note that as of 3.5, this constructor expects exactly one exception object in the given array, with all other array positions being null. The restriction may be lifted in the future, and clients of this class must not make this assumption.

    • Method Detail

      • getReferences

        public IWorkbenchPartReference[] getReferences()
        Returns an array of part references, containing references of parts that were intialized correctly. Any number of elements of the returned array may have a null value.
        Returns:
        the part reference array

      • getExceptions

        public PartInitException[] getExceptions()
        Returns an array of exceptions, corresponding to parts that could not be intialized correctly. At least one element of the returned array will have a non-null value.
        Returns:
        the exception array
